{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Around 72,108 identified entities and 258,264 words make up the corpus.",
    "Resume [56] The Resume dataset is based on the CV-Oriented Chinese dataset, which was made public by Purdue University and contains eight entity types, including title (TITLE), country (CONT), organization name (ORG), profession (PRO), location name (LOC), race (RACE), person name (NAME), and educational background (EDU).",
    "MSRA [56] In the entity classifications of location name, institution name, and person name, the MSRA dataset on Chinese NER from Microsoft Research Asia (MSRA) is made up approximately 50,000 Chinese entity recognition annotations.THE GENIA [56] THE GENIA dataset has been taken from the biomedical literature, which helps with bio-text mining system development.",
    "The dataset includes the collection of 1999 abstracts from systems that analyze and retrieve medical literature in which three medical subject terms such as human, blood cell, and copy factor that are used to gather the abstracts.",
    "This dataset may be applied in the development and evaluation of natural language processing (NLP) tools and algorithms, particularly text categorization and named entity recognition."
  ],
